The paper introduces a new genetic algorithm technique called gene expression programming, which is used for creating computer programs. The paper covers a wide range of problems, including symbolic regression, sequence induction, block stacking, cellular automata rules, and boolean concept learning. These problems are typically associated with the sub-categories of genetic programming (cs.GP), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
